The paper deals with the problem of choosing a multi-winner rule, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also uses methods from the theory of approximation algorithms (cs.DS) and provides a quantitative analysis of the performance of different multi-winner rules, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between diversity and individual excellence, which is a topic in social informatics (cs.SI).
